valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Guild Suggestion Pool</span><hr size=1> Hello all, I felt is was time I get some o' my ideas out there and get everyone else to pitch in as well. Now, since the guild seems to be at a turning point, I think we should all, collectively, decide its direction. Don't worry, I'm not suggesting a coup or anything, calm down.<br>
Alright, here are some suggetions. I think that we need a bigger vault. More items to help out not only our members but other people as well. I'm talking even little things. Right now we have what, about a dozen items? If we had each guild member, even new ones, donate something to the guild it would be a better incentive for people to join our guild. (Since most people who play EQ only do so for the items). What I'm talking about here is sort of a &quot;need a penny, take a penny&quot; idea. Also, we could give out some higher lvl items, even lvl 15+ to newbies and tell them to spread the word of our &quot;benevolence&quot; but in a much less arrogant way. =) <br>
When I first joined the guild, I thought of the Benevolent Order as almost a player-run supplement to EQ's Guide/GM system. Where we help people without looking for bugs in the program or anything, we remove the burueacracy from the system to actually help people, not just our own guild. If anyone else thinks this is a better direction for us, speak out, I'm trying to draw out the ideas of everyone here. (Mostly because I don't think I can make Friday's guild meeting/raid.)<br>
If anyone has any other suggestions, let us know, especially on the member board where all of our members can get to the ideas eventually.<br>
<br>
Idella, lvl 15 bard<br>
aka Kavin, of the screwed over lvl of 19<br>
